## Project Structure

```
type-novel/
├── public/
│   └── books/              ← drop .txt files here
│       └── MyBook.txt
├── src/
│   └── Main.purs           ← entire application, single module
├── index.html
├── style.css
├── vite.config.js
├── spago.yaml
├── flake.nix
└── package.json
```

---

## Getting Started

### With Nix

```bash
nix develop
spago build
npx vite
```

### Without Nix

```bash
npm install
spago build
npx vite
```

Open `http://localhost:5173` in any modern browser.

### Adding a Book

```bash
cp ~/path/to/my-novel.txt public/books/

# Add one entry to availableBooks in Main.purs:
# , { file: "my-novel.txt", label: "My Novel" }

spago build
```

The `cleanText` pipeline normalises smart quotes, em dashes, ellipses,
and all non-printable characters automatically. `.txt` files from
Project Gutenberg work without any preprocessing.

---

## Controls

| Action        | How                                                     |
|---------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Type          | Just type — the hidden textarea captures all keystrokes |
| Backspace     | Removes the last character                              |
| Reset chunk   | Reset button                                            |
| Next chunk    | Next button, or Enter/Space on the results screen       |
| Change size   | 150 / 300 / 500 buttons (applies on next load)          |
| Toggle theme  | Light Mode / Dark Mode button                           |

---

## Chunk Sizes

| Size | Approx. chunks for a novel | Feel                                 |
|------|----------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| 150  | ~4600                      | Short bursts, quick wins             |
| 300  | ~2300                      | Default, good flow state             |
| 500  | ~1400                      | Longer sessions, fewer interruptions |

Select the size before clicking Load Book. It applies to the chunking
pass on load and cannot be changed mid-session without reloading.

---

## CSS Themes

Both themes are implemented as CSS custom property scopes on the root
container. The entire palette switches with one `className` write on the
container div — no JavaScript loops, no inline style mutations.

```css
.typing-trainer-container.dark  { --bg: #000; --correct: #3a9e52; ... }
.typing-trainer-container.light { --bg: #f2efe9; --correct: #1e7a38; ... }
```

---

## Character States

| Class            | Meaning                | Display                         |
|------------------|------------------------|---------------------------------|
| `char-not-typed` | Not yet reached        | Dim                             |
| `char-cursor`    | Next character to type | Beam caret, blinking when idle  |
| `char-correct`   | Typed correctly        | Green                           |
| `char-incorrect` | Typed wrong character  | Red underline, shows typed char |

Incorrect positions show the character the user actually typed rather
than the target character. Backspace restores the position to untyped.

---

## Vite Configuration

`appType: "mpa"` is required. Without it Vite's SPA fallback returns
`index.html` for any path that doesn't match a known module, which means
`fetch("/books/mybook.txt")` silently returns your app HTML instead of
the file. The `loadTextFile` function includes a guard that detects this
and returns a readable error message if it happens.

```javascript
// vite.config.js
export default defineConfig({
  appType: "mpa",   // disables SPA catch-all fallback
});
```
